# Tests Manual

This manual explains how to run all tests for the **Stock Inventory App** on Linux.

## 1) Test types in this project

The project currently uses **JavaScript-based testing** (not Python):

- **Backend unit/API tests**: Jest
- **Frontend tests**: React Scripts test runner (Jest under the hood)
- **End-to-end (E2E) tests**: Playwright

---

## 2) Repository structure (relevant parts)

- `backend/`
  - `package.json`
  - `jest.config.js`
  - `tests/*.unit.test.js`
  - `tests/*.api.test.js`
- `frontend/`
  - `package.json`
  - `tests/e2e/*.spec.js`
  - `src/...`

---

## 3) Backend tests (Jest)

From the backend folder:

```bash
cd backend
npm install
```

Available commands:

```bash
npm test            # Run all backend tests
npm run test:unit   # Run unit tests only
npm run test:api    # Run API tests only
npm run test:watch  # Watch mode
npm run test:coverage
```

---

## 4) Frontend tests (React/Jest)

From the frontend folder:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm test
```

---

## 5) E2E tests (Playwright)

From the frontend folder:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm install --save-dev @playwright/test
npx playwright install --with-deps
npm run e2e
```

Optional headed/UI modes (if scripts exist):

```bash
npm run e2e:headed
npm run e2e:ui
```

---

## 6) If using Docker containers

If app/test files changed, rebuild before testing:

```bash
docker compose down
docker compose build --no-cache
docker compose up -d
```

Then run tests again.

---

## 7) Common troubleshooting

## A) `npm ERR! ENOTEMPTY ... rename ... node_modules/...`
Clean and reinstall:

```bash
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm cache clean --force
npm cache verify
npm install --no-audit --no-fund
```

## B) Playwright trace command says "too many arguments"
You passed multiple files with wildcard. Use one file:

```bash
npx playwright show-trace "test-results/<single-test-folder>/trace.zip"
```

## C) `show-trace` fails on headless server/EC2
Use artifacts instead:
- `test-results/.../error-context.md`
- `test-results/.../test-failed-1.png`
- `test-results/.../video.webm`

Or copy traces locally and open on
